Romney is only GOP senator not on new White House coronavirus task force Trump taps members of Congress to advise on reopening MORE (Utah) is the only Republican senator not on a congressional task force created by the White House to study reopening parts of the country shuttered by the coronavirus.
A spokeswoman for Romney and a source familiar confirmed that the GOP senator was not asked to take part in the task force.
Romney was the only GOP senator to vote for one of the articles — abuse of power — during the Senate impeachment trial earlier this year.
Romney wasn't the only senator not included on the new White House task force.
